INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1,1,now(),now(),'<img class=\"alignright\" src=\"/wp-content/themes/twentyseventeen/assets/images/automate_all_the_things.png\" width=\"150\" />I just can\'t express my excitement without sounding just a tad nutty. I\'m truly stoked that Ansible installed WordPress this simply with this one little playbook. And this playbook dynamically allocates my server variables based on the hostname. This is so cool that I\'m getting just a bit faint.\r\n\r\nI really hope you enjoy this playbook as much as I do and that it provides you <em><strong>hours of enjoyment</strong></em>. Wait. On second thought, this should only provide <strong>minutes</strong> of enjoyment -- because if it takes hours, then Ansible isn\'t really doing the heavy lifting, is it?\r\n\r\nAnother thing I love about Ansible is the amazing <a href=\"http://docs.ansible.com/ansible/modules_by_category.html\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>module documentation</strong></a>.  The learning curve to Ansible is very small!.  Within minutes, you can be building your own custom Ansible playbooks and deploying stuff.  And as your brain starts coming up with new cool ways to use Ansible, the docs sure help!\r\n<blockquote>Perhaps the \"hours of enjoyment\" refers to the fun you\'ll have reading the documentation and exploring new ways to enjoy Ansible and Ansible Tower.</blockquote>\r\nWhatever amount of time it takes you to enjoy this, I thank you for taking the time to read this rambling post. Enjoy!','Ansible Playbooks FTW!','','publish','open','open','','ansible-playbook-install','','',now(),now(),'',0,'http://{{ webhostname }}/?p=1',0,'post','',1);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2,1,now(),now(),'This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://{{ webhostname }}/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','publish','closed','open','','sample-page','','',now(),now(),'',0,'http://{{ webhostname }}/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0);
